The scrollbar is almost certainly coming from a parent Telerik container:

.k-window-content
    └─ .k-edit-form-container
           ├─ popup-container
           └─ k-edit-buttons

Your measurements also show:

popup-container = 379
k-edit-buttons = 8.6
----------------------
total ≈ 388

while:

k-window-content = 486

So the content is actually smaller than the available area.

This usually means Telerik has:

overflow-y: scroll;

forced on one of the containers.

Find the culprit

Run:

console.log(
    $(".k-window-content:visible").css("overflow")
);

console.log(
    $(".k-window-content:visible").css("overflow-y")
);

console.log(
    $(".k-edit-form-container:visible").css("overflow")
);

console.log(
    $(".k-edit-form-container:visible").css("overflow-y")
);

My guess:

.k-window-content {
    overflow-y: scroll;
}

or

.k-edit-form-container {
    overflow: auto;
}
Quick test (Javascript)

Paste this after popup opens:

$(".k-window-content:visible").css({
    overflow: "hidden"
});

$(".k-edit-form-container:visible").css({
    overflow: "hidden"
});

If the scrollbar disappears immediately, we found it.

